findings.pleural_effusions: Bilateral small pleural effusions, right greater than left, with associated compressive atelectasis.
findings.liver: Enhances homogeneously without focal lesion or intrahepatic biliary duct dilation.
findings.gallbladder: No stone, wall thickening, edema, or pericholecystic fluid.
findings.pancreas: Enlarged and edematous with surrounding fat stranding and trace free fluid.
findings.pancreatic_duct: Upper limits of normal, measuring 3 mm.
findings.lymph_nodes: Regional lymph nodes enlarged, measuring up to 7 mm.
findings.kidneys: Symmetric nephrograms, excretes contrast promptly, 1.8 cm simple cyst in the right kidney.
findings.GI: Stomach decompressed, small and large bowel within normal limits, small amount of free fluid in the right paracolic gutter.
findings.retroperitoneum: Normal aorta with minimal atherosclerotic calcifications.
findings.pelvis: Normal urinary bladder, no pelvic lymph node enlargement, calcified uterine fibroid measuring 1.6 cm.
findings.osseous_structures: No focal lesions suspicious for malignancy, multilevel degenerative changes of the thoracolumbar spine.
